# Linux / SSH / Homelab Cheatsheet

Comandos úteis para SSH, gerenciamento de portas, homelab, serviços e backup.

---

# SSH

## Conectar no homelab

```bash
ssh -i ~/.ssh/id_homelab je@homelab-cwbs
```

---

## Configuração SSH

Adicionar chave pública no servidor:

```bash
~/.ssh/authorized_keys
```

Adicionar chave privada no cliente:

```bash
~/.ssh/id_iotag
```

Configuração do `~/.ssh/config`:

```ssh
Host iotag
    HostName 10.1.10.212
    User leo
    IdentityFile ~/.ssh/id_iotag
```

---

# Serviços

## Reiniciar sistema

```bash
sudo reboot
```

---

## Desligar monitor do servidor

```bash
sudo vbetool dpms off
```

---

# Portas

## Ver processos usando uma porta

```bash
sudo lsof -i :8006
```

---

## Pegar apenas os PIDs

```bash
sudo lsof -t -i :8006
```

---

## Matar tudo na porta

```bash
sudo lsof -t -i :8006 | xargs -r sudo kill -9
```

---

## Verificar se a porta ainda está aberta

```bash
sudo ss -tulnp | grep :8006
```

---

## Alias killport

```bash
alias killport='f() { sudo lsof -t -i :$1 | xargs -r sudo kill -9; }; f'
```

Uso:

```bash
killport 8006
```

---

# DNS / Porta 53

## Iniciar systemd-resolved

```bash
sudo systemctl start systemd-resolved
sudo systemctl enable systemd-resolved
```

---

## Parar systemd-resolved

```bash
sudo systemctl stop systemd-resolved
sudo systemctl disable systemd-resolved
```

---

# Tailscale

## Gerar certificado

```bash
sudo tailscale cert homelab-cwb.tail613c98.ts.net
```

---

# Dotfiles

## Backup incluindo arquivos ocultos

```bash
shopt -s dotglob
cp -r .* dotfiles/
shopt -u dotglob
```

---

## Salvar lista de aplicativos instalados

### Debian / Ubuntu

```bash
dpkg --get-selections | awk '$2 == "install" {print $1}' > ~/dotfiles/pkg-list.txt
```

---

# Git

## Alterar remote do GitLab

```bash
git remote set-url origin https://oauth2:TOKEN@gitlab.com/projetos-pessoais5523809/homelab-dotfiles.git
```

---

# Troubleshooting

| Problema | Solução |
|---|---|
| Porta ocupada | `sudo lsof -i :PORTA` |
| Processo travado | `killport PORTA` |
| SSH não conecta | Verifique `~/.ssh/config` |
| DNS quebrado | Reinicie `systemd-resolved` |
| Git remoto errado | `git remote set-url origin URL` |

---

# Dicas úteis

| Dica | Comando |
|---|---|
| Ver portas abertas | `ss -tulnp` |
| Ver processos | `htop` |
| Ver discos | `lsblk` |
| Ver RAM | `free -h` |
| Ver CPU | `lscpu` |

